Color in preserved specimens . The only difference we observed in the coloration of this species between the two localities at which it was found is a prominent, dark anterior nasal tube in almost all specimens from the Amirante Islands (
Fig. 9
), whereas the specimens from the Chagos Archipelago have anterior nasal tubes that are either pale, or have a small amont of dusky pigment at the tips (
